title: Chinese New Year Day Parade
description: Children and young adults hold up banners as they parade through Chinatown in Portland, Oregon. The children are followed by a New Year’s Lion, who collects goodwill money offerings that hang above shop windows along Southwest Second Avenue. Sounds of firecrackers, tom toms and cymbals accompany the celebration of the New Year. Oregon Journal photographs.
